  "caption": "AI agents are getting their own internet. And two protocols are making it happen.\n\nAt the center: MCP (Model Context Protocol) by Anthropic and A2A (Agent to Agent) by Google.\n\nMCP connects agents to tools and data. Think of it as USB for AI. It went from 100K downloads in late 2024 to 97 MILLION monthly SDK downloads by end of 2025.\n\nA2A connects agents to each other. It launched with 50+ partners including Salesforce, PayPal, and Atlassian.\n\nBoth protocols are now governed by the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation, co founded by OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Microsoft, AWS, and Block.\n\nWhat's coming next: agent marketplaces in H2 2026 where you can plug in third party AI agents like SaaS subscriptions.\n\nWe're watching the TCP/IP moment for AI happen in real time.\n\n#AI #MCP #A2A #AIAgents #AgenticAI",
